snippet: Mrs. Green, a teenage officers’ mess waitress, signed up in the last months of the war and recalled the officers’ courtly behavior.
abstract: Florence Green, member of Britain's Royal Air Force who was believed to be the last surviving veteran of World War I, dies at age 110.
lead_paragraph: Mrs. Green, a teenage officers’ mess waitress, signed up in the last months of the war and recalled the officers’ courtly behavior.
